Our basic beehive starter kit is uniquely designed and made in Canada to:
‚Ä¢ Provide adequate equipment for starting your beekeeping adventure;
‚Ä¢ Help you keep your brood safe from dampness and condensation;
‚Ä¢ Give your bees a better chance at controlling intruders access to the hive;
‚Ä¢ Make your beekeeping operation easier;

It is made with the workmanship and quality of design that is the trademark of EmotionsinWood

This basic starter kit contains the following components:
‚Ä¢ One regular bottom board and entrance reducer ‚Äì assembled;
‚Ä¢ One inner cover ‚Äì assembled;
‚Ä¢ One outer cover ‚Äì assembled;
‚Ä¢ One deep brood box - to be assembled;
‚Ä¢ One medium honey super - to be assembled;
‚Ä¢ Nails for assembling the boxes;

CUSTOMIZE YOUR KIT:
"MAKE IT YOUR FIRST SUMMER PACKAGE and save shipping cost‚Äù by adding the components that you will need this summer onto your basic kit:
Select one of the following options:
‚Ä¢ Simply buy a basic kit and be ready to receive your bees - Select: "Basic Kit"
‚Ä¢ Add a second deep ‚Äúbrood‚Äù box - Select: "Option 1 (2nd BBox)"
‚Ä¢ Add a second ‚Äúhoney super‚Äù box - Select: "Option 2 (2nd HSupr)"
‚Ä¢ Add both a second deep ‚Äúbrood‚Äù box and a second ‚Äúhoney super‚Äù - Select: "Both Option 1 + 2"
‚Ä¢ Replace the regular bottom board by a screened bottom board - Select: "Option 3 Screen Btm"
‚Ä¢ Add all 3: a second deep ‚Äúbrood‚Äù box plus a second ‚Äúhoney super‚Äù plus a screened bottom board; - Select: "Options 1+2+3"


Assembly and nailing instructions: See the short 3 minutes video on Utube: https://youtu.be/cUdIppeliuM

Components and custom features description:

The basic bottom board (with entrance reducer)
‚Ä¢ It is made of a spruce frame and a plywood board;
‚Ä¢ It is equipped with a spruce landing strip which channel the rain to drip away from the hive;
‚Ä¢ Our design ensures that no plywood is sticking out and rotting in the rain;
‚Ä¢ This bottom board comes with an entrance reducer which you can set as desired to 20 or 50 mm wide entrance allowing your bees to control intruders more easily;
‚Ä¢ Special entrance reducer holders prevent you from pushing the entrance reducer inside the hive by accident;
‚Ä¢ This bottom board will be what you will use on day one and during the fall and winter;

The screened bottom board
‚Ä¢ Comes with the same entrance reducer;
‚Ä¢ It is made of a spruce frame;
‚Ä¢ The screen is a durable galvanized 1/8" mesh;
‚Ä¢ The removable tray is made of a non-rotting corrugated plastic sheet;
‚Ä¢ This screened bottom board enables a great air flow throughs the hive during the summer season;
‚Ä¢ The screen lets mites fall through onto the removable plastic tray below where you will be able to regularly monitor the level of infestation;


The brood box (deep box)
‚Ä¢ It fits standard deep (9 6 ¬º‚Äù) frames;
‚Ä¢ Made of ‚Äúeasy-to-assemble-by-hand‚Äù finger joined spruce boards;
‚Ä¢ All nail holes are pre-drilled. The box assembly and nailing is made easy as 1,2,3;
‚Ä¢ Frame rests are made of maple rails. Frame rests are pre-installed on all front and back boards of your boxes for durability. This also provides a space to slide in a frame lifter tool thus enabling you to easily lift the frames from the box;
‚Ä¢ Each box is equipped with a groove on every side providing you an easy and efficient grip on your precious boxes;

The honey super (medium box)
‚Ä¢ It fits standard medium (6 ¬º‚Äù) frames;
‚Ä¢ It is entirely made in Canada;
‚Ä¢ Made of ‚Äúeasy-to-assemble-by-hand‚Äù finger joined spruce boards;
‚Ä¢ All nail holes are pre-drilled. The box assembling and nailing is made easy as 1,2,3;
‚Ä¢ Frame rests are made of maple rails. Frame rests are pre-installed on all front and back boards of your boxes for durability. This also provides a space to slide in a frame lifter tool thus enabling you to easily lift the frames from the box;
‚Ä¢ Each box is equipped with a groove on every side providing you an easy and efficient grip on your precious boxes;

The inner cover
‚Ä¢ It is built of a sturdy spruce frame and board
‚Ä¢ The frame has a notch on one side to provide air flow and allow bee passage.
‚Ä¢ It can be used either with the exit up or down depending on the season and on your preference;
‚Ä¢ The holes in the inner cover accept PORTER BEE ESCAPES. This will allow you to use the inner cover between brood box and honey super for clearing the honey super of bees when it is time to harvest honey:

The outer cover
‚Ä¢ It is made from a spruce frame with a plywood board;
‚Ä¢ It is clad with aluminum. No plywood is exposed to the rain and no rain can find its way into the hive;
‚Ä¢ It is designed with a hole facing the inner cover opening, which ensures a good air flow and an easy bee traffic;
